The paper deals with distributed optimization algorithms for large-scale machine learning problems, which are typically studied in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), distributed computing (cs.DC), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of submodular functions is also a common theme in these areas, which further supports these categories.
